QUALIFICATION: nomenclaturally invalid name; Coutière created S. metaneomeris as a replacement species name for what he had previously described as S. neomeris streptodactylus Coutière, 1905, but then reused the name streptodactylus to denote a new subspecies of metaneomeris differing from the original concept; given he wished to recognise two subspecies, the species name streptodactylus should have been retained, and the present taxon given a new subspecies name; this is the reason for the action of Banner & Banner (1966) in proposing the new name S. streptodactylus hadrungus
